        <h2 id="cake">Recipe #1</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 30-45 min</li>
            <li>Serves: sweet for tea</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>eggs</td>
                    <td>3-4</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                   <td>granulated sugar</td>
                    <td>360g</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>margarine</td>
                    <td>180g</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>baking powder</td>
                    <td>15-17g</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>flour</td>
                    <td>350-400g</td>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Take 3 eggs and break them, then add 180 g of sugar to the container and mix.Then add melted margarine to it.After a good mixing add flour and baking powder knead the dough
</p>
<p><strong>Step 2:</strong> We will make a filling. For the filling, pour sour cream over the container, again add 180 g of sugar to it, mix well, add 1 egg and 3 teaspoons mix everything and the filling is ready
</p>
<p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Roll out the dough in the form, pour the filling and send it to the oven for 30 to 45 minutes at 250 degrees
</p>
     <h2 id="beshbarmak">Recipe #2</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 3-3,5 hours</li>
            <li>Serves: meal</li>
        </ul>
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th><strong>Ingredients</strong></th>
                    <th><strong>Quantity</strong></th>
                </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td>meat</td>
                    <td>1kg or more(1 plate for 4 people)</td>
                </tr>
                 <tr>
                    <td>onions</td>
                    <td>1-2pieces</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>noodles</td>
                    <td> 350-400g</td>
                </tr>
               <tbody>
               </tbody>
            </thead>
        </table>
        
    
         <p class="besh"><strong>Step 1:</strong>We take a certain amount of meat and put it in a container and pour water. put it in the fire until it boils. After boiling, we will clean the soup from meat bubbles </p>

<p class="besh"><strong>Step 2:</strong> After boiling, dilute the heat and leave for 2 hours at this time, peel and cut the onion and prepare the sauce
</p>
<p class="besh"><strong>Step 3:</strong>After 2 hours, we separate the meat from the soup and put noodles in the same soup and cook after cooking, we combine them all </p>

<!--all recipes is written in my experience -->
        
